caption: I’m an out of towner (from Chicago) and my husband and I came here twice within the span of two days. Need I say more? Lunch was about $25 per person with two sashimi over rice and add-ons (Uno, scallop, oysters). Everything is incredibly fresh and satisfying. I recommend the fatty tuna, king salmon, and oysters. The spicy poke definitely has a kick to it. Everything is made/sliced/shucked to order. Worth every dollar. An honor to be served by the actual Maguro brothers! This is a must try if you are in the area!
Ordered the King salmon sushi bowl and poke; both were incredible quality and so tasty.
Food is good but parking is not  friendly

A must. The best poke in Oahu

Fabulous fish. Fresh and seasoned beautifully. Can never go wrong with Maguro Brothers. It's not the greatest atmosphere, the shop is tucked inside an Asian grocery in Kekaulike market. But the food is worth it. There are small tables with some seating but not for large groups. Staff work this location and the one on Nahua street.  Poke is served a bit more Japanese style so less saucy, allowing you to really taste the freshness of the fish. A must in Honolulu.

Excellent ingredients prepared with skill, though the ambiance might not be for everyone.  This location is a stall at an indoor meat and vegetable market. Directly across the walkway is a vendor with an array of fresh chicken and pork. The floors are cement typical of one of these markets, ready to be hosed down at the day's end. I felt comfortable and totally assured of the cleanliness of my food and the table I sat down to eat at, but if you're particularly squeamish, perhaps you'd enjoy another Maguro Brothers outpost more.  I purchased the chirashi and maguro mix bowls along with a side of scallops, and found the quality to be basically the opposite of those surroundings. Excellent cuts of each fish, letting the delicate flavors of each shine. Rice cooked perfectly, sprinkled lightly with soy sauce, green onions, strips of nori. Good quality gari.
Best grilled salmon I’ve had in my life!! Highly recommend!!

To the owner: From my observation while waiting for my food, I can see there is way to improve your efficiency for a quicker turn around.  Just mount a web cam and watch yourself work for an hour. By just re-organizing the rice station, cutting station and POS can reduce cross path situation and gain efficiency.  Sometimes downtowner can't wait that extra 5 minutes. Besides, they already spend an extra 15 minutes to walk down here.  FYI.  Vegetable and Ahi is down to 2 minutes wait.  But to be fair, they have 8 people working in the kitchen.  Here you have only three.  The brothers and the lady.
